namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.

transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the on Print shop tutorials.
In today's video, we will introduce you to the save draft functionality and it's working in our new upgraded content editor.
This feature allows you to save your work in progress without publishing it, ensuring you don't lose any of your hard work.
To get started, let's open the product description screen.
Start adding some content for the long description to.
You'll notice an edit icon appearing in the editor toolbar whenever you make changes to the content.
You can simply click on the edit icon and then select the Save Draft option.
This will save your current work as a draft, which you can come back to and edit later.
If you don't find the save draft relevant, you can even choose to discard the draft.
Your work will also be saved automatically everyone minute, ensuring that your progress is secure.
Before finalizing your work, you can preview the content on the front store using the preview icon.
When you finalize the content after preview, you can click on the save button from the top to publish the content.
All the published contents will be saved as versions with timestamps in the system, which can be accessed from the Version History option within the editor.
Please note that the latest 3 versions of the published content will be saved in the editor for the respective section from the version history drop down.
You can choose to switch to any of the available versions and continue editing.
Once you switch to any of the available versions, the current content from the editor will be lost.
That's it.
Using the Save Draft mode is a great way to ensure that your work is always saved and that you can pick up right where you left off.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
